main event: A sighting of an unidentified flying object took place near Tacoma, Washington on April 13, 1951.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at an enormous speed, traveling straight up., The observation lasted for about 2 minutes., Witnesses included military personnel and a civilian supervisor., The object's heading was from southwest to northeast, then northwest., There was no positive identification of the object, and it was described as potentially being a balloon or aircraft.
witness description: military personnel and a civilian supervisor from Tacoma, Washington
